# ERP Global List UI Standard

**Phase:** ERP GLOBAL UI.5 — Universal List UI Standard Rule (2026-07-02)
**Status:** RULE APPROVED FOR REVIEW — not yet applied system-wide
**Visual reference:** `/dms/documents` — All Documents list screen

---

## Purpose

Define one consistent ERP list/table UX for every module — implemented and future — so users can scan, find, filter, and open records with the same visual language everywhere.

This rule extracts the approved pattern from the live **All Documents** screen. Cursor must not invent a new list design. When in doubt, match All Documents.

**Related rules (must also be followed):**
- `.cursor/rules/erp-combobox-standard.mdc` — filter dropdowns with DB/async options
- `.cursor/rules/erp-workspace-tabs-standard.mdc` — Rule 17 (list state caching)
- `.cursor/rules/erp-dropdown-zindex-standard.mdc` — combobox/popover stacking
- `docs/standards/ERP_GLOBAL_UI_UX_FORM_TABLE_DRAWER_DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md` — §11 Combobox, §15 Table/List

---

## Approved Visual Reference

> **The All Documents list screen is the approved visual reference for ERP list screens.**
> All current and future ERP lists must match its search bar style, filter panel style, icon style, spacing, colors, row style, action style, toolbar style, and overall visual behavior unless a documented exception is approved.

**Canonical reference files:**
| Role | Path |
|------|------|
| Page shell | `src/app/(protected)/dms/documents/page.tsx` |
| List/table UI | `src/features/dms/documents/dms-documents-table.tsx` |
| Page header | `src/components/erp/page-header.tsx` (`ERPPageHeader`) |
| Status badges | `src/features/dms/documents/dms-document-status-badge.tsx` |
| Sort headers | `src/components/erp/table/sort-col-header.tsx` |
| Pagination | `src/components/erp/table/table-pagination.tsx` |
| Column resize hook | `src/components/erp/table/use-resizable-columns.ts` |
| Sort/paginate hook | `src/hooks/use-sort-paginate.ts` |
| Shared enterprise table | `src/components/erp/table/erp-data-table.tsx` (`ERPDataTable`) |

---

## Applies To

- All workspace list routes (`tabKind: "list"`) in every ERP module
- DMS, Party Master, HR, Admin, Finance Basics, Geography, UOM, Reports, Audit, and future modules
- Both `ERPDataTable`-based lists and custom `<table>` lists (All Documents uses a custom table today)

---

## Non-Goals

This rule does **not** govern:
- Record/detail/workspace forms (`ERPRecordWorkspaceForm`) — see `erp-record-workspace-form-standard.mdc`
- Child add/edit dialogs (`ERPChildDialogForm`) — see `erp-child-dialog-form-standard.mdc`
- App-wide command palette / Ctrl+K global search — see UI guide §30
- Mobile-native list apps — desktop-first ERP; responsive-safe but not mobile-app conversion

---

## Core Principle

> **Lists are for scanning, finding, filtering, and opening records.**
> Forms, drawers, detail pages, profile pages, or expandable detail panels are for full record details.

ERP lists often have many database fields. **Do not show every field as a default column.** Show summary data in the list; show full detail after the user opens the record.

---

## List Page Layout

Every list page must:

1. Render inside the workspace content area with consistent outer padding:
   ```tsx
   <div className="p-6 space-y-4">
   ```
2. Use `ERPPageHeader` for title, optional description, and breadcrumbs:
   ```tsx
   <ERPPageHeader
     title="All Documents"
     description="Browse, search, and manage all DMS documents."
     breadcrumbs={[{ label: "DMS", href: "/dms" }, { label: "All Documents" }]}
   />
   ```
3. Wrap the list body in `space-y-4` vertical rhythm (search row → filter row → table → footer count).
4. **Never** cause full-page horizontal overflow. Horizontal scroll, if needed, must stay **inside** the table container only (`overflow-x-auto` on the table wrapper).
5. Register the route in `src/lib/workspace/workspace-route-registry.ts` with `tabKind: "list"` and `singleton: true` where appropriate.

---

## Search Bar and Toolbar Standard

All Documents uses a **two-row toolbar**. All ERP lists must follow this pattern (Row 2 may be omitted only when a screen has zero filters).

### Row 1 — Search + primary actions

```tsx
<div className="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
  {/* optional mode selector / left controls */}
  <div className="relative flex-1 min-w-[200px]">
    <Search className="absolute left-2.5 top-2.5 h-3.5 w-3.5 text-muted-foreground" />
    <Input
      placeholder="Search by number, title, description..."
      value={search}
      onChange={(e) => setSearch(e.target.value)}
      className="pl-8 h-8 text-sm"
    />
  </div>
  <div className="ml-auto flex items-center gap-2 shrink-0">
    <Button variant="outline" size="sm"><RefreshCw className="h-3.5 w-3.5" /></Button>
    <Button size="sm" className="gap-1.5"><Plus className="h-3.5 w-3.5" /> New …</Button>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Required tokens (match All Documents):**

| Element | Classes / behavior |
|---------|-------------------|
| Search input height | `h-8` |
| Search input text | `text-sm` |
| Search icon | `lucide-react` `Search`, `h-3.5 w-3.5`, `left-2.5 top-2.5`, `text-muted-foreground` |
| Input left padding | `pl-8` (room for icon) |
| Toolbar gap | `gap-2` |
| Refresh button | `variant="outline" size="sm"`, icon-only acceptable |
| Primary create action | `size="sm"`, icon + label, `gap-1.5`, icons `h-3.5 w-3.5` |
| Action cluster | `ml-auto flex items-center gap-2 shrink-0` |

### Row 2 — Labeled searchable filters

When filters exist, wrap them in a bordered panel (All Documents pattern):

```tsx
<div className="rounded-lg border border-border bg-muted/10 p-3">
  <div className="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-3">
    <div>
      <label className="mb-1 block text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground">
        Type
      </label>
      <ERPCombobox
        value={filterType}
        onValueChange={…}
        options={typeOptions}
        placeholder="All Types"
        searchPlaceholder="Search document types..."
        allowClear
        triggerClassName="h-8 text-xs"
      />
    </div>
    {/* repeat per filter */}
  </div>
</div>
```

**Filter rules:**
- **Every filter must have a visible label** above the control (`text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground`).
- **Database/async filter options → `ERPCombobox`** (never shadcn `<Select>`). See `erp-combobox-standard.mdc`.
- Static small enums (e.g. search mode with 6 fixed values) may use shadcn `<Select>` with `h-8 text-xs` trigger — All Documents uses this for search mode only.
- Combobox trigger in filters: `triggerClassName="h-8 text-xs"`, `allowClear` for optional filters.
- Additional filters must fit the same grid/panel — do not invent a second filter layout style.

### Active filter chips (required when filters are used)

When any filter is active, show removable chips below the filter grid:

```tsx
<div className="mt-3 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5 border-t border-border/60 pt-3">
  <Badge variant="secondary" className="gap-1 pr-1 text-[11px] font-normal">
    Type: Passport
    <button type="button" …><X className="h-2.5 w-2.5" /></button>
  </Badge>
  <button type="button" className="text-[11px] text-muted-foreground hover:underline">Clear all</button>
</div>
```

### Result count (recommended)

Below the table, show filtered vs total when client-side filtering is used:

```tsx
<div className="text-xs text-muted-foreground">
  Showing {filteredCount} of {totalCount} …
</div>
```

