## Table/List Container Standard

```tsx
<div className="rounded-md border border-border overflow-x-auto">
  <table className="w-full text-xs table-fixed">…</table>
  <TablePagination … />
</div>
```

| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Outer container | `rounded-md border border-border overflow-x-auto` |
| Table density | `text-xs` |
| Layout algorithm | `table-fixed` (prevents runaway column width / page overflow) |
| Header row | `border-b border-border bg-muted/30` |
| Body row | `border-b border-border hover:bg-muted/20 transition-colors` |
| Cell padding | `px-3 py-2` |
| Header cell padding | `px-3 py-2` (SortColHeader default is `px-4 py-2.5` — All Documents overrides to `px-3 py-2`) |

**Primary identifier column:** `font-mono font-medium text-primary`, clickable with `hover:underline truncate`.

**Title/summary column:** primary line `font-medium truncate`; optional secondary line `text-muted-foreground truncate mt-0.5` (italic for AI summary in DMS).

**Empty/missing cell value:** em dash `—` in `text-muted-foreground`.

---

## Column Strategy

**Do not show every database field as a list column.**

### Default column pattern

```text
Primary identifier / reference / code
Name / title / description summary (1–2 lines max in list)
Type / category
Status badge
Important date (expiry, due, updated — pick one primary date)
Owner / company / person (when applicable)
Actions (fixed width, right-aligned)
```

### What belongs off-list

Move to record detail, drawer, expandable row, or column-visibility menu:
- Long descriptions, AI summaries beyond one truncated line
- Internal IDs, audit metadata, JSON blobs
- Rarely used secondary fields
- Confidentiality / internal flags unless business-critical for that list

All Documents default columns (approved): **Doc No, Title, Type, Status, Expiry, Tags, Actions**.

---

## Sorting, Filtering, and Pagination

### Sorting

- Important columns must be sortable via clickable headers.
- Use `SortColHeader` + `useSortPaginate` for custom tables, or TanStack sorting via `ERPDataTable`.
- Sort indicator icons: `ArrowUp` / `ArrowDown` when active, `ArrowUpDown opacity-35` when inactive — all `h-3 w-3`.

### Filtering

- Client-side filter for small/medium in-memory lists (All Documents today).
- Server-side filter/search for large datasets — never load unbounded records into the browser.

### Pagination

- Use `TablePagination` (All Documents) or built-in `ERPDataTable` pagination.
- Default page size: **25** (options: 10, 25, 50, 100).
- Show range: `{from}–{to} of {total}` with first/prev/next/last icon buttons (`h-7 w-7` ghost icons, `h-3.5 w-3.5` chevrons).

---

## Column Width and Visibility

### Column resizing (required where practical)

- Drag header right edge to resize (`cursor-col-resize`, `hover:bg-primary/50` handle).
- Custom tables: `useResizableColumns` + `SortColHeader` `width` + `onResizeStart`.
- `ERPDataTable`: built-in TanStack column resizing.
- Persist widths per browser via `localStorage` when a stable `storageKey` / `tableId` is available.

### Column visibility (required for wide lists)

- Lists with more than ~8 possible columns must offer show/hide controls.
- `ERPDataTable`: use built-in `ERPColumnMenu`.
- Custom tables: add equivalent column-visibility menu before UI.5A pilot if needed.

### Actions column

- Fixed width (~104px in All Documents), not resizable.
- Right-aligned icon button group.

---

## Icons and Row Actions

**Icon library:** `lucide-react` (default for all ERP lists).

| Context | Size |
|---------|------|
| Toolbar / filter row icons | `h-3.5 w-3.5` |
| Row action button icons | `h-3 w-3` |
| Empty-state icon | `h-8 w-8 opacity-30` |
| Search bar icon | `h-3.5 w-3.5` |

### Row action pattern (All Documents — canonical)

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-1 justify-end">
  <Button size="icon" variant="ghost" className="h-6 w-6" title="Open">
    <ExternalLink className="h-3 w-3" />
  </Button>
  <Button size="icon" variant="ghost" className="h-6 w-6" title="Archive">
    <Archive className="h-3 w-3" />
  </Button>
  <Button size="icon" variant="ghost" className="h-6 w-6 text-destructive hover:text-destructive" title="Delete">
    <Trash2 className="h-3 w-3" />
  </Button>
</div>
```

**Rules:**
- Icon-only row actions **must** have `title` (tooltip) or `aria-label`.
- Destructive actions use `text-destructive hover:text-destructive` — never casual inline delete without confirmation.
- Prefer inline ghost icon buttons for 2–3 common actions; use dropdown menu only when >3 actions or actions are rarely used.
- **Never** nest `<Button>` inside `<DropdownMenuTrigger>` — style `DropdownMenuTrigger` directly (see workspace save-close standard Rule 2).

