## Status Badges

Use `Badge variant="outline"` with compact list sizing:

```tsx
className="text-[10px] font-semibold px-1.5 py-0.5 border"
```

### Approved semantic color map (extend per module, keep hues consistent)

| Status | Tailwind pattern (light) |
|--------|--------------------------|
| Active | `bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 border-blue-200` |
| Draft | `bg-slate-100 text-slate-700 border-slate-200` |
| Pending / Pending Review | `bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 border-amber-200` |
| Approved | `bg-green-100 text-green-700 border-green-200` |
| Rejected / Failed | `bg-red-100 text-red-700 border-red-200` |
| Expired | `bg-orange-100 text-orange-700 border-orange-200` |
| Expiring Soon | orange/amber variant (module-specific component OK) |
| Inactive / Archived | `bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 border-gray-200` |
| Suspended / Blocked | red or slate variant — pick one per module, document in module constants |
| Completed / Renewed / Superseded | `bg-purple-100 text-purple-700 border-purple-200` |
| AI Draft / AI Suggested | `bg-violet-100 text-violet-700 border-violet-200` |
| AI Reviewed | violet or amber depending on workflow stage |

**Rule:** The same business status must look the same across HR, DMS, Admin, Parties, Fleet, and future modules. Define module badge components that reuse these hue families — do not invent new colors per screen.

Reference: `src/features/dms/documents/dms-document-status-badge.tsx`

