## Empty, Loading, and Error States

### Empty (in-table — All Documents pattern)

```tsx
<td colSpan={N} className="text-center py-10 text-muted-foreground">
  <div className="flex flex-col items-center gap-2">
    <FileText className="h-8 w-8 opacity-30" />
    <p className="text-sm">No documents found</p>
    <Button size="sm" variant="outline" className="mt-1 gap-1.5">
      <Plus className="h-3.5 w-3.5" /> Create first …
    </Button>
  </div>
</td>
```

- Centered, muted, module-appropriate lucide icon, short message, optional primary CTA when user can create.

### Loading

- Inline: `Loader2 className="h-4 w-4 animate-spin"` + muted helper text.
- Row skeleton or table overlay acceptable for server refetch; do not flash empty state during load.

### Error

- Bordered alert: `rounded-md border border-destructive/30 bg-destructive/5 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-destructive`.
- Preserve user's search/filter state after error.

---

## Permission-Aware Actions

- UI actions must respect module permissions **and** backend/RLS enforcement.
- Do not show actions as enabled when the server will reject them.
- Prefer **hide** for unavailable create/delete; **disable + title reason** acceptable for row actions when context-dependent.
- Destructive / irreversible actions (delete, deactivate, approve, reject, merge, send email) **require confirmation** (`confirm()` minimum; `AlertDialog` preferred).
- AI-generated changes remain **human-review-first** — no auto-save, auto-approve, auto-delete, or auto-merge unless an explicitly approved workflow says otherwise.

---

## Responsive and Overflow Behavior

- Lists are **desktop-first** but must not break the app on narrow viewports.
- Table horizontal overflow stays inside `overflow-x-auto` container — never on `<body>`.
- Filter grid degrades: `grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-5`.
- On very narrow screens: fewer visible columns, horizontal scroll, or card-style summaries are acceptable if documented — critical actions must remain reachable.
- Toolbar wraps with `flex-wrap` — primary actions stay in `ml-auto shrink-0` cluster.

---

## Existing Screens Migration Rule

- Migrate existing list screens **gradually** — do not rewrite all lists in one pass.
- **UI.5A pilot:** apply to **one** non-DMS list screen first; compare side-by-side with All Documents before wider rollout.
- Preserve existing business logic, server actions, permissions, filters, and workflows during UI-only migration.
- `ERPDataTable` lists: align toolbar/filter/chip styling to All Documents; table chrome may already match via shared component — verify visually.
- Custom table lists: adopt All Documents two-row toolbar + table tokens explicitly.

---

## Future Screens Rule

- Every **new** ERP list screen must follow this standard from day one.
- No new module may introduce a custom list/search/table visual language without an approved documented exception.
- Prefer shared building blocks:

| Need | Component |
|------|-----------|
| Full-featured list | `ERPDataTable` + unique `tableId` |
| Custom list (DMS-style) | `SortColHeader`, `TablePagination`, `useSortPaginate`, `useResizableColumns` |
| Page header | `ERPPageHeader` |
| Filters (DB options) | `ERPCombobox` |
| List state cache | `ERPDataTable` prefs or `useWorkspaceTableState` |

---

## Implementation Requirements

1. **Read All Documents first** before building or migrating any list.
2. **Page shell:** `p-6 space-y-4` + `ERPPageHeader`.
3. **Toolbar:** two-row pattern (search row + labeled filter panel + chips).
4. **Table container:** `rounded-md border border-border overflow-x-auto`.
5. **No page-level horizontal scroll.**
6. **Sort + paginate** on all non-trivial lists.
7. **Column resize** where ≥5 data columns.
8. **Column visibility** where many optional columns exist.
9. **Persist** search/page/sort/column prefs per workspace tab rules (Rule 17).
10. **Register** route in workspace route registry.
11. Cross-check `erp-combobox-standard.mdc` for all filter dropdowns.

---

## QA Checklist

Use after implementing or migrating any list screen:

- [ ] Visually matches All Documents search row (input height, icon, spacing, action buttons)
- [ ] Filter panel uses labeled `ERPCombobox` controls in bordered `bg-muted/10` panel
- [ ] Active filter chips + Clear all work correctly
- [ ] Table container: `rounded-md border`, no full-page horizontal overflow
- [ ] Header row: `bg-muted/30`; body rows: `hover:bg-muted/20`
- [ ] Primary code column: mono, primary color, clickable
- [ ] Row actions: ghost `h-6 w-6` icon buttons, `h-3 w-3` icons, tooltips present
- [ ] Destructive actions require confirmation
- [ ] Status badges use compact outline badge pattern
- [ ] Sorting works on key columns; sort icons visible
- [ ] Column resize works (where applicable); widths persist if configured
- [ ] Column visibility works (where applicable)
- [ ] Pagination shows correct range and page controls
- [ ] Empty state: centered icon + message + optional CTA
- [ ] Loading state does not flash false empty results
- [ ] Error state visible and non-destructive to filter state
- [ ] Unauthorized actions hidden or disabled correctly
- [ ] Narrow viewport: layout wraps/degrades without breaking workspace chrome
- [ ] Business logic, permissions, and server actions unchanged after UI migration
- [ ] Workspace tab switch preserves list UI state (search, page, sort)

---

## Documented Exceptions

Exceptions require explicit approval note in the phase implementation report:
- Read-only audit/log viewers with no create action
- Embedded pickers / sub-lists inside record forms (not primary module lists)
- AI/semantic search result panels (card layout) — All Documents AI/Semantic modes are acceptable secondary layouts tied to the same list screen
